And you are CORRECT.<br>
<br>
What's happening in this thread is a mutation of a standard line of logic for the VERY UBER.<br>
<br>
Laoke or Lenardo or Denzalo ... those monks don't need much more AC. So they look at HPs over AC for two reasons. 1) The items they're upgrading with are going to have either comprable AC to what they're already wearing or 2) so many MORE HPs to what they're wearing that the AC loss won't be much of an issue.<br>
<br>
However ... <br>
<br>
You are correct. When soloing, AC is much more efficient than it's being given credit for.<br>
<br>
Gaudy numbers of HPs INCREASE downtime.<br>
<br>
Your regeneration and hp recovery RATE is the same no matter how many HPs you have. So the lesser number of HPs you have, the less downtime you have regenning or binding wounds.<br>
<br>
If you have a CLERIC BOT, this point is moot as CH is a factor.<br>
<br>
If you have any other type of healer bot though, as Korph stated in his pre-CH cleric analogy, mana efficiency is an issue, and again, LESS HPs help more.<br>
<br>
If you're going it totally solo, then yes, MORE HPs aren't exactly needed. MORE Regen, Better DPS and Higher AC are what's needed. Because that's what will increase your effectiveness.<br>
<br>
And against your regular ole standard dark blue mob, who doesn't flurry or have astronomically HIGH ATK ratings, the higher AC (even though past the mythical cap it has a lower rate of return) is still useful.<br>
<br>
For RAIDS ... MORE HP.<br>
<br>
For SOLO ... MORE DPS, REGEN AND AC.<br>
<br>
HPs are still needed obviously. But to be efficient, you need to see the whole picture. Your job is to kill the monsters fast and efficiently and the efficiency comes from finding that perfect balance between HP loss and time spent recovering HPs.<br>
<br>
Nothing underscores this MORE for me than when I put my fungi on my warrior alt for a week and solo'd with him. When he had LESS HPs and higher STR and DEX (he had a proccing weapon) he solo'd MUCH more effectively. His downtime was reduced by about a minute or two. And so I killed more mobs per hour and got more XP per hour. <br>
<br>
OF COURSE, what sucks now is that soloing is less rewarding than it used to be, and it's usually much better to just group ... AND SOMETHING PEOPLE TOTALLY FORGET about XP grouping is that if you're not pulling and you're not tanking ... your AC and your HPs don't matter at all as you ought to be able to avoid aggro at least 90 percent of the time. All that matters sometimes is your DPS.<br>
<br>
You are a monk. You have different jobs. You have different tools for those jobs. Be flexible. And don't lock yourself into the standard idea that to be a better monk you absolutely HAVE to have more HPs. Cause sometimes that's not your job. <p><img src=http://wubao.freewebspace.com/images/wubao.gif>
